# LDCPortfolio Architecture Patterns Rule

Apply these patterns when adding or modifying functionality.

## Current Architecture Shape

- Single-page React app composed from section components in `src/sections`.
- App-level providers in `src/context` handle cross-section state (theme and music).
- Reusable design-system style primitives live in `src/components/ui`.
- Feature behavior is extracted to custom hooks in `src/hooks` when reused.

## Component and State Patterns

- Keep section components focused on presentation and local interaction.
- Put cross-cutting, multi-component state in context providers rather than prop drilling.
- Use hooks for shared behavior; avoid duplicating effect logic across sections.
- Keep provider APIs small, typed, and explicit (for example `toggleTheme`, `playTrack`).

## Styling and UI Patterns

- Use Tailwind utility classes and existing CSS variables for theme-safe styling.
- Prefer composing existing UI primitives before creating new base components.
- Preserve responsive behavior and animation quality when editing layouts.

## i18n and Content Patterns

- Any new user-facing copy should be added to locale dictionaries (`en.json`, `vi.json`).
- Keep translation keys semantic and grouped by feature/section.
- Avoid embedding long hardcoded copy directly in components when localization is expected.

## Change Placement Rules

- New page block: add under `src/sections` and compose in `src/App.tsx`.
- New reusable UI primitive: add under `src/components/ui`.
- New global app behavior: add/update a provider in `src/context`.
- New shared utility: place in `src/lib` or `src/hooks` based on responsibility.

